message.content:
A crab is a type of crustacean with a hard exoskeleton and ten legs.
Their body is flattened and divided into a cephalothorax and an abdomen.
Most crabs have two claws, with one being larger than the other.
They come in a range of colors, including brown, red, and blue.
Crabs can typically be found in oceans, estuaries, and along coastlines.
Their distinctive sideways movement is due to their legs being attached to the sides of their body.
Crabs are often used for food and can be found in many seafood dishes.
